<chained to table my a thick metal mesh wire. It appears well used. Many hands have paged through this tome>



This book describes many manufacturing techniques of magical wares. It deals mostly with mundane means of manipulating metals and artifacts to be used as base materials. It stresses the separation of materials, lest all be used up in the process of conversion and the importance of careful consideration of what final product is being made.

It seems of vital neccessity to make sure that a craftmaster understands that multiple manufacture is difficult. Magical energies often get sidetracked if more than one of an item is being made. Even simple devices such as darts can take more than is actually needed if the crafter has other base materials on their person.


<the carpet on which you stand is covered with stains and folded piles of bags, sacks and debris. It appears many have used it to organize their inventories.>
